name: launchdarkly_flutter_client_sdk
desc:
launchdarkly_flutter_client_sdk provides a Flutter wrapper around the LaunchDarkly mobile SDKs for
Android and iOS.

name: LDClient
desc: The main interface for the LaunchDarkly Flutter SDK.

name: alias
desc: Alias associates two users for analytics purposes.

name: allFlags
desc: Returns a map of all feature flags for the current user, without sending evaluation events to LaunchDarkly.

name: boolVariation
desc: Returns the value of flag flagKey for the current user as a bool.

name: boolVariationDetail
desc: Returns the value of flag flagKey for the current user as a bool, along with information about the resultant value.

name: close
desc: Permanently shuts down the client.

name: doubleVariation
desc: Returns the value of flag flagKey for the current user as a double.

name: doubleVariationDetail
desc: Returns the value of flag flagKey for the current user as a double, along with information about the resultant value.

name: flush
desc: Triggers immediate sending of pending events to LaunchDarkly.

name: getConnectionInformation
desc: Returns information about the current state of the SDK's connection to the LaunchDarkly.

name: identify
desc: Changes the active user context.

name: intVariation
desc: Returns the value of flag flagKey for the current user as an int.

name: intVariationDetail
desc: Returns the value of flag flagKey for the current user as an int, along with information about the resultant value.

name: isInitialized
desc: Checks whether the SDK has completed starting.

name: isOffline
desc: Returns whether the SDK is currently configured not to make network connections.

name: jsonVariation
desc: Returns the value of flag flagKey for the current user as an LDValue.

name: jsonVariationDetail
desc: Returns the value of flag flagKey for the current user as an LDValue, along with information about the resultant value.

name: registerFeatureFlagListener
desc: Registers a callback to be notified when the value of the flag flagKey is updated.

name: registerFlagsReceivedListener
desc: Registers a callback to be notified when flag data is received by the SDK.

name: setOnline
desc: Shuts down or restores network activity made by the SDK.

name: start
desc: Initialize the SDK with the given LDConfig and LDUser.

name: startFuture
desc: Returns a future that completes when the SDK has completed starting.

name: stringVariation
desc: Returns the value of flag flagKey for the current user as a string.

name: stringVariationDetail
desc: Returns the value of flag flagKey for the current user as a string, along with information about the resultant value.

name: track
desc: Track custom events associated with the current user for data export or experimentation.

name: unregisterFeatureFlagListener
desc: Unregisters an LDFlagUpdatedCallback from the flagKey flag.

name: unregisterFlagsReceivedListener
desc: Unregisters an LDFlagsReceivedCallback.

name: LDConfig
desc: A configuration object used when initializing the LDClient.

name: allAttributesPrivate
desc: Whether the SDK is configured to never include user attribute values in analytics requests.

name: autoAliasingOptOut
desc: Whether the SDK is configured to not send automatic alias events.

name: backgroundPollingIntervalMillis
desc: The configured background polling interval in milliseconds.

name: connectionTimeoutMillis
desc: The configured connection timeout in milliseconds.

name: diagnosticOptOut
desc: Whether the SDK is configured to not send diagnostic data to LaunchDarkly.

name: diagnosticRecordingIntervalMillis
desc: The configured diagnostic recording interval in milliseconds.

name: disableBackgroundUpdating
desc: Whether the SDK is configured to disable polling for feature flag values when the application is in the background.

name: evaluationReasons
desc: Whether the SDK is configured to request evaluation reasons to be included in flag data from the service.

name: eventsCapacity
desc: The configured event capacity.

name: eventsFlushIntervalMillis
desc: The configured event flush interval in milliseconds.

name: eventsUri
desc: The configured URI for eventing requests.

name: inlineUsersInEvents
desc: Whether the SDK is configured to send the entire LDUser object to the service in every event.

name: maxCachedUsers
desc: The count of users to store the flag values for in on-device storage.

name: mobileKey
desc: The configured mobile SDK key.

name: offline
desc: Whether the SDK is configured not to connect to LaunchDarkly on LDClient.start.

name: pollUri
desc: The configured URI for polling requests.

name: pollingIntervalMillis
desc: The configured foreground polling interval in milliseconds.

name: privateAttributeNames
desc: The configured set of attributes to never include values for in analytics requests.

name: stream
desc: Whether the SDK is configured to use a streaming connection when in the foreground.

name: streamUri
desc: The configured URI for stream requests.

name: useReport
desc: Whether the SDK is configured to use the HTTP REPORT verb for flag requests.

name: LDConfigBuilder
desc: A builder for LDConfig.

name: LDConfigBuilder
desc: Create a new LDConfigBuilder for the given mobile key.

name: allAttributesPrivate
desc: Configures the SDK to never include optional attribute values in analytics events.

name: applicationId
desc: A unique identifier representing the application where the LaunchDarkly SDK is running.

name: applicationVersion
desc:
A unique identifier representing the version of the application where the LaunchDarkly SDK is
running.

name: autoAliasingOptOut
desc: Set to true to opt out of sending automatic alias events.

name: backgroundPollingIntervalMillis
desc: Sets the interval between background flag poll requests.

name: build
desc: Create an LDConfig from the current configuration of the builder.

name: connectionTimeoutMillis
desc: Sets the connection timeout for network requests.

name: diagnosticOptOut
desc: Set to true to opt out of sending diagnostics data.

name: diagnosticRecordingIntervalMillis
desc: Set the interval at which periodic diagnostic data is sent.

name: disableBackgroundUpdating
desc: Disables or enables background polling requests for flag values.

name: evaluationReasons
desc: Configure whether the SDK will request evaluation reasons to be included in flag data from the service.

name: eventsCapacity
desc: Set the capacity of the event buffer.

name: eventsFlushIntervalMillis
desc: Sets the maximum amount of time in between sending analytics events to LaunchDarkly.

name: eventsUri
desc: Sets the URI for eventing requests.

name: inlineUsersInEvents
desc: Sets whether the SDK will send the entire LDUser object to the service in every event.

name: maxCachedUsers
desc: Sets how many users to store the flag values for in on-device storage.

name: offline
desc: Disables or enables network calls from the LaunchDarkly client.

name: pollUri
desc: Sets the URI for polling requests.

name: pollingIntervalMillis
desc: Sets the interval between foreground flag poll requests.

name: privateAttributeNames
desc: Sets a Set of private attributes to never include the values for in analytics events.

name: stream
desc: Enables or disables real-time streaming flag updates.

name: streamUri
desc: Sets the URI for stream requests.

name: useReport
desc: Configure whether the SDK should use the HTTP REPORT verb for flag requests.

name: LDConnectionInformation
desc: Describes the connectivity state of the SDK, and information on occurrence of request failures and successes.

name: LDConnectionInformation
desc: Constructor for LDConnectionInformation

name: connectionState
desc: The connectivity state of the SDK.

name: lastFailedConnection
desc: The time at which lastFailure occurred, if ever.

name: lastFailure
desc: The most recent failure the SDK has encountered.

name: lastSuccessfulConnection
desc: The most recent time that new flag values were received, if ever.

name: LDConnectionState
desc: Enumerated type defining the possible connection states for the SDK.

name: values
desc: A constant List of the values in this enum, in order of their declaration.

name: LDErrorKind
desc: Enumerated type defining the defined error cases for an LDEvaluationReason with the kind LDKind.ERROR.

name: values
desc: A constant List of the values in this enum, in order of their declaration.

name: LDEvaluationDetail
desc:
Class returned by the "variation detail" methods such as LDClient.boolVariationDetail, combining the result of
the evaluation with an explanation of how it was calculated.

name: LDEvaluationDetail
desc: Constructor for LDEvaluationDetail.

name: reason
desc: An object describing the primary reason for the resultant flag value.

name: value
desc: The result of the flag evaluation.

name: variationIndex
desc: The index of the returned flag within the list of variations if the default value was not returned.

name: LDEvaluationReason
desc: Describes the reason that a flag evaluation produced a particular value.

name: error
desc: Returns an LDEvaluationReason with the kind LDKind.ERROR and the given errorKind.

name: errorKind
desc: The type of the error responsible when the kind is LDKind.ERROR.

name: fallthrough
desc: Returns an LDEvaluationReason with the kind LDKind.FALLTHROUGH.

name: inExperiment
desc: Whether the rule or fallthrough is part of an experiment when kind is LDKind.RULE_MATCH or LDKind.FALLTHROUGH.

name: kind
desc: The general category for the reason responsible for the evaluation result.

name: off
desc: Returns an LDEvaluationReason with the kind LDKind.OFF.

name: prerequisiteFailed
desc: Returns an LDEvaluationReason with the kind LDKind.PREREQUISITE_FAILED and the given prerequisiteKey.

name: prerequisiteKey
desc: The key of the first prerequisite that failed when kind is LDKind.PREREQUISITE_FAILED.

name: ruleId
desc: The id of the rule that match the user when kind is LDKind.RULE_MATCH.

name: ruleIndex
desc: The index of the rule that match the user when kind is LDKind.RULE_MATCH.

name: ruleMatch
desc: Returns an LDEvaluationReason with the kind LDKind.RULE_MATCH and the given ruleIndex and ruleId.

name: targetMatch
desc: Returns an LDEvaluationReason with the kind LDKind.TARGET_MATCH.

name: unknown
desc: Returns an LDEvaluationReason with the kind LDKind.UNKNOWN.

name: LDFailure
desc: Describes an error encountered during an attempt to retrieve flag values from the LaunchDarkly service.

name: LDFailure
desc: Constructor for an LDFailure.

name: failureType
desc: The type of the failure.

name: message
desc: A message describing the failure.

name: LDFailureType
desc: Enumerated type defining the defined failures the SDK can report encountering while fetching flag values.

name: values
desc: A constant List of the values in this enum, in order of their declaration.

name: LDFlagUpdatedCallback
desc: Type of function callback used by LDClient.registerFeatureFlagListener.

name: LDFlagsReceivedCallback
desc: Type of function callback used by LDClient.registerFlagsReceivedListener.

name: LDKind
desc: Enumerated type defining the possible reasons for a flag evaluation result, used in LDEvaluationReason.

name: values
desc: A constant List of the values in this enum, in order of their declaration.

name: LDUser
desc: An LDUser contains the attributes of a user context.

name: anonymous
desc: Whether this user is anonymous.

name: avatar
desc: The user's avatar attribute.

name: country
desc: The user's country attribute.

name: custom
desc: The user's custom attributes.

name: email
desc: The user's email attribute.

name: firstName
desc: The user's firstName attribute.

name: ip
desc: The user's ip attribute.

name: key
desc: The user's key.

name: lastName
desc: The user's lastName attribute.

name: name
desc: The user's name attribute.

name: privateAttributeNames
desc: Which of the user's attributes are specified to be private.

name: secondary
desc: The user's secondary attribute.

name: LDUserBuilder
desc: A builder for constructing LDUser objects.

name: LDUserBuilder
desc: Creates a new builder with the specified user key.

name: anonymous
desc: Sets whether the user is anonymous.

name: avatar
desc: Sets the user's avatar attribute.

name: build
desc: Constructs an LDUser instance from the values currently in the builder.

name: country
desc: Sets the user's country.

name: custom
desc: Adds a new custom attribute to the user.

name: email
desc: Sets the user's email attribute.

name: firstName
desc: Sets the user's first name attribute.

name: ip
desc: Sets the user's ip attribute.

name: lastName
desc: Sets the user's last name attribute.

name: name
desc: Sets the user's name attribute.

name: privateAvatar
desc: Sets the user's avatar attribute, marking it as private.

name: privateCountry
desc: Sets the user's country, marking it as private.

name: privateCustom
desc: Adds a new custom attribute to the user, marking it as private.

name: privateEmail
desc: Sets the user's email attribute, marking it as private.

name: privateFirstName
desc: Sets the user's first name attribute, marking it as private.

name: privateIp
desc: Sets the user's ip attribute, marking it as private.

name: privateLastName
desc: Sets the user's last name attribute, marking it as private.

name: privateName
desc: Sets the user's name attribute marking it as private.

name: privateSecondary
desc: Sets the user's secondary attribute, marking it as private.

name: secondary
desc: Sets the user's secondary attribute.

name: LDValue
desc: An immutable instance of any data type that is allowed in JSON.

name: operator ==
desc: The equality operator.

name: booleanValue
desc: Returns this value as a bool if the type matches, otherwise returns false.

name: buildArray
desc: Starts building an array value.

name: buildObject
desc: Starts building an object value.

name: codecValue
desc: Returns a raw platform representation of the value.

name: doubleValue
desc: Returns this value as a double if the value is numeric, otherwise returns 0.

name: fromCodecValue
desc: Constructs a value from an arbitrary platform value.

name: get
desc: Retrieves an array element by index.

name: getFor
desc: Retrieves an object element by index.

name: getType
desc: Returns the type of this value.

name: hashCode
desc: The hash code for this object.

name: intValue
desc: Returns this value as an int if the value is numeric, otherwise returns 0.

name: keys
desc: Enumerates the property names in an object, returns an empty iterable for all other types.

name: normalize
desc: Returns the same value if non-null, or ofNull if null.

name: numValue
desc: Returns this value as a num if the value is numeric, otherwise returns 0.

name: ofBool
desc: Returns an instance for a bool value.

name: ofNull
desc: Returns an instance for a null value.

name: ofNum
desc: Returns an instance for a numeric value.

name: ofString
desc: Returns an instance for a string value.

name: size
desc: Returns the number of elements in an array or object, returns 0 for all other types.

name: stringValue
desc: Returns this value as a String if the type matches, otherwise returns an empty string.

name: values
desc: Enumerates the property values in an array or object, returns an empty iterable for all other types.

name: LDValueArrayBuilder
desc: Builder for constructing an LDValueType.ARRAY typed LDValue.

name: addBool
desc: Append a bool value to the builder.

name: addNum
desc: Append a numeric value to the builder.

name: addString
desc: Append a String value to the builder.

name: addValue
desc: Append an LDValue to the builder.

name: build
desc: Returns an LDValue of type LDValueType.ARRAY containing the builder's current elements.

name: LDValueObjectBuilder
desc: Builder for constructing an LDValueType.OBJECT typed LDValue.

name: addBool
desc: Associated the given key and bool in the builder.

name: addNum
desc: Associated the given key and num in the builder.

name: addString
desc: Associated the given key and String in the builder.

name: addValue
desc: Associated the given key and LDValue in the builder.

name: build
desc: Returns an LDValue of type LDValueType.OBJECT containing the builder's current elements.

name: LDValueType
desc: Describes the type of an LDValue. These correspond to the standard types in JSON.

name: values
desc: A constant List of the values in this enum, in order of their declaration.
